                        <locus from="106">(fol. 106)</locus>
                        <author key="person_41951136">Willelmus Peraldus</author>
                        <title key="work_1917">Summa de uitiis et uirtutibus</title>
                        <incipit type="prol.">Presens opus habet quinque partes</incipit>
                        <incipit type="text">Cum circa utilia studere debeamus</incipit>
                        
                        <note>Part of an elaborate treatise on Virtues, in five parts (part 1 on
                        virtue in general; part 2 on the three theological virtues; part 3 on the four
                        cardinal virtues; part 4 on spiritual gifts; and part 5 on the beatitudes)
                       The  manuscript ends (unfinished) with the words 'amentur que amanda' in the 16th chapter of the second book, the verso of
                        the last leaf being left blank.
                        </note>
                        
                        <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
